    "body": "### Problem\n\nIn nightly build, if I create a vsplit window, then scroll the right buffer by typing \"j\" or \"ctrl-d\", half of the left window will scroll together with the right window. I have to \"ctrl-l\" to redraw. See screen recording of the issue.\n\nv0.11.6 does not have this issue.\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/137211a5-56a7-449c-9c7a-590e6b53506e\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean some_file\n:vsplit\nctrl-w, l to focus on the right window\nctrl-d multiple times to scroll the right window down\nyou will see the left window is split and the right part starts to scroll with the right window\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nscroll should not affect other windows.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-2500+ge8e694d837\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim 9.1.1752\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 26.3.1 (25D2128)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwezterm 20240203-110809-5046fc22\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbob install nightly",
